{%- comment -%}
  Carousel Object
    Object for generating a carousel.

  Usage:
    This is expected to be combined with the matching o-carousel stylesheet and
    the objects/widgets/carousel.ts scripts file for initialization. This
    simplifies the process of creating a site wide, standard carousel.

    I understand that this component is not useful in all scenarios, e.g. those
    where a carousel is bespoke for a section, but it is sufficient for most of
    the common content section carousels.

  Modifying:
    This carousel tool includes common controls for arrows, progress bars and 
    such. Modifying should be done in the form of replacing assets or tweaking
    the stylesheet.
  
  Params:
    slides - Captured HTML string of divs, inserted to where slides are expected
    class - Container class (optional).
    attr - Container attribute (optional).
    progress - If true, include a progress bar. Defaults false.
    progressClass - Progress bar class (optional).
    arrows - If true, add control arrows. Defaults false.
  
  Version:
    1.0.0 - 2021-06-05
{%- endcomment -%}
<div class="o-carousel {{ class | default: '' }}" data-carousel {{ attr | default: '' }}>
  <div class="o-carousel__carousel">

    {%- if arrows -%}
      <button type="button" class="o-carousel__arrow is-left has-js" data-carousel-left>
        {%- render 'icon.arrow-left' -%}
      </button>
    {%- endif -%}

    <div class="o-carousel__carousel-slides" data-carousel-slides>
      {{- slides -}}
    </div>

    {%- if arrows -%}
      <button type="button" class="o-carousel__arrow is-right has-js" data-carousel-right>
        {%- render 'icon.arrow-right' -%}
      </button>
    {%- endif -%}
    
    <div class="o-carousel__hider"></div>
  </div>
  
  {%- if progress -%}
    <div class="o-carousel__progress {{ progressClass | default: '' }}">
      <div class="o-carousel__progress-inner">
        <div data-carousel-progress></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  {%- endif -%}
</div>